The Death Star is an Imperial moon-sized military battlestation armed with a planet-destroying superlaser.

It is the first in a long series of superweapons developed to execute the Tarkin Doctrine, but whose concept had been explored even before the Clone Wars. The Death Star was designed to allow Emperor Palpatine to more directly control the Galactic Empire through fear. They are always commanded by a Moff.

Charros IV is an arid planet in the Mid Rim with high plateaus, snow-capped mountains, and black-water lakes. Its Xi Char cathedral factories were infiltrated by Raith Sienar 45 BBY; the Xi Charrians were infuriated when he was exposed as an infidel. The planet's government remained loyal to the Galactic Republic during the Clone Wars, and did not understand the Republic's objection to the cathedral factories manufacturing Vulture droids for the Confederacy of Independent Systems; to the Xi Charrians, these were works of art. Haor Chall Engineering was headquartered on the planet, but abandoned the world after being attacked during the Clone Wars by the Republic.

Togoria is a planet with grassy plains, dense forests and rolling hills, and is the homeworld of the Togorians. Humans are not permitted on the planet uninvited unless they crashed (crashing was only allowed once). The planet originally joined the Confederacy of Independent Systems and later allied with the Rebel Alliance.

Kashyyyk also known as Wookiee Planet C, Edean, G5-623, and Wookiee World, is the lush, wroshyr-tree-filled home planet of the Wookiees. A Mid-Rim world, it is a member of the Galactic Republic and later enslaved by the Galactic Empire.

With no axial tilt and a perfectly circular orbit, Kashyyyk experiences no seasons. It is composed of a molten metallic core, rocky mantle, and a silicate rock crust. The planet has four continents, making up 40% of the surface, which is mostly covered in lush, tree-filled forests, although the planet did have a small amount of desert region in the rain-shadow of its small mountain ranges. A tropical ocean belt contains strings of islands and long coral reefs. In addition, a few sandy beaches can be found along the shores of its oceans.

Kwenn is the Kwenn system's main planet, orbited by Kwenn Space Station. Kwenn is in the Mid Rim, perhaps near Relgim Sector, near the inner border of the Outer Rim. Kwenn is the homeworld of Arndall Lott. It is currently a willing part of the Empire.

Sriluur, in the Outer Rim Territories near Hutt Space, is the homeworld of the Weequay. It is on the Sisar Run, near the Ac'fren Spur. Its continents are covered in white, rocky deserts, with cities along the shores of its bountiful seas and oceans. The natives worshiped Quay, the planet's main moon, as a god, and practice astrology.

The Weequay were allied to the Hutts in the Third Battle of Vontor, but were not enslaved by the Hutts. Sriluur joined the Galactic Republic. Houks colonized the planet in 282 BBY, and were constantly at conflict with the natives. By 11 BBY a full scale civil war broke out between the Houks and the Weequay. Just reccently, in 1 BBY, the planet was conquered by the Galactic Empire, ending the interspecies war.

Honoghr is the homeworld of the Noghri, near Kessel. Seven planets orbit the Honoghr sun, from tiny Logru with its oceans of boiling lava, to distant Kuthul, the frozen giant. Of these seven worlds, it was the fourth planet that was blessed with life.

Kessel is a planet located in Kessel Sector, in the Outer Rim Territories, near Hutt Space and the dangerous celestial bodies of the Maw. It is a prison world, and is home to the galaxy's largest spice mining operation. Under Imperial rule, slave labor is in extensive use.

Kintan is the home world of the Niktos. After a supernova explosion near the system, evolution of the Nikto divided into five subspecies. Kintan is located within the Si'Klaata Cluster, on the Ac'fren Spur.

Kintan striders, also found around the galaxy as pets of Hutts, were originally from Kintan. However, they were driven to extinction on the planet itself.

Klatooine is the arid home world of the Klatooinians. It is located within the Si'Klaata Cluster, under Hutt control. It is covered with deserts and, to a lesser extent, savannas.

It is home to the Derelkoos Desert, the location of a fissure that spurted a fountain of liquid wintrium. No technology is allowed one kilometer around this Fountain of Ancients, which the Klatooinians revere as a holy site.

The planet was taken over by the Hutts under the Treaty of Vontor in 25,100 BBY. Klatooine is ruled by the Council of Elders. The Hutts, however, control all Klatooinian activities offworld. The Klatooinian Trade Guild formed on Klatooine 4,995 BBY.

Jabiim is a world deluged by torrential rains, experiencing less than five days per standard year without precipitation. Its muddy surface constantly shifted from the weight of the rains. Jabiim is also rich in ore, although their valuable ores are currently dwindling. During the Clone Wars, Jabiim was a world that the Galactic Republic ignored until it was too late.

The world has a very unstable electric field, and electric storms are quite common. Due to this, repulsor craft of any type are largely unusable on the planet.

Iego is a planet located in the Extrictarium Nebula in the Outer Rim Territories. Due to the obscurity of the Nebula, Iego does not appear on any starcharts. Iego does not orbit a sun; rather, it is warmed by local stellar gases. It is home to the subterranean Maelibi species, as well as thousands of stranded spacefarers who have been lured to the planet by the Diathim -- a spaceworthy species that resides on Iego's forty-two moons. Although Iego appears to have no noteworthy natural resources, the concepts of aging and hunger somehow elude its residents.

In spacer lore, Iego is considered a mythical location, and is the subject of many stories and rumors. Numerous expeditions set out to find the planet, though few succeed, and the ones who do were for the most part unable to leave. Due to the amount of hearsay surrounding the planet, as well as its continued unconfirmed location, most members of the galaxy's scientific community dismissed Iego as a spacefarer's tale.

Mon Calamari (known as Dac in Mon Calamarian and Quarrenese, and sometimes also called Calamari) is a planet in the Calamari system of the Calamari Sector, located in the Outer Rim. It is home to a wealth of sentient species: the Mon Calamari, the Quarren, the Moappa, the Amphi-Hydrus, and the Whaladons. Mon Calamari is the name given to the planet by Human explorers from the Galactic Republic who first discovered and revealed the world to the rest of the galaxy. The native species refere to the planet as Dac. The planet is a shining bluish-white orb from space, due to its ocean-covered surface. It is home to 27.5 billion Mon Calamarians and Quarren, as well as the impressive Mon Calamari Shipyards.

The Cron Drift is a giant asteroid field located just "south" of the Perlemian Trade Route within the Auril Sector of the Outer Rim Territories. It once was a small nebula of considerable beauty and dynamics; however, during the Great Sith War, a sabotaged ancient Sith device used to manipulate matter within the cores of stars caused the detonation of the nearby Cron Cluster stellar group.

All planetary bodies in the vicinity were smashed, with the debris becoming scattered throughout the region. The greatest concentration formed the famed asteroid field itself, and it held a reputation as a hiding place for all sorts of activity such as pirating, looting, and smuggling of illicit materials.

Ossus is the third planet in the Adega system in the Auril Sector. Originally a rich, lush world, Ossus was ravaged into an arid and toxic planet with the destruction of the Cron Cluster.

Ossus was an important Jedi site for over twenty-five millennia, serving as a repository of knowledge and a center for learning for the Old and New Jedi Orders alike. In the latter years of the Old Republic and beyond, it was home to the tribal Ysanna, descendants of Jedi who had survived the Cron supernova. The planet came under attack by the Sith in 3,996 BBY.

Belderone is the sector capital of Belderone Sector, on the Perlemian Trade Route, with 2 inhabited moons. Belderone and Kulthis both have Stenax colonies. The reason the Stenaxes colonized these planets is unknown. They remain isolated from the other inhabitants, on Belderone settling a previously uinhabited continent.

Drongar is a mostly uninhabitable tropical planet in the Outer Rim Territories, with the native airborne spores causing death to those who are not protected from them. The climate is characterized by common monsoons with devastating electrical storms, soaring temperatures, and humidity over 90%. There is also a large atmospheric oxygen content. The planet has two small moons and is located in the system with three other planets. Natural features of Drongar included the Sea of Sponges and the Qarohan Steppes.

The planet was discovered by Nikto scouts 220 BBY. During the Clone Wars, this planet became important and was fought over by both the Galactic Republic and the Separatists due to being the only planet that could produce bota, a highly valuable miracle drug. When the bota mutated and became worthless, both forces pulled out of Drongar 20 BBY.

Kulthis was a planet in the Belderone system that was the site of a Rebel Alliance base.

Belderone and Kulthis both had Stenax colonies. The reason the Stenaxes colonized these planets is unknown. They remained isolated from the other inhabitants

randosha was an arboreal planet located in the galaxy's Mid Rim and the homeworld of the Trandoshan species. It was orbited by Wasskah, a verdant moon, and was positioned in the same star system as Kashyyyk, the homeworld of the Trandoshans' fierce rivals, the Wookiees. The feared Trandoshan bounty hunter Bossk hailed from Trandosha.

Thanos was a planet located in the Togoria system of the Taldot sector. During the Clone Wars, the planet was located within Separatist space. During the Imperial Period, it contained an Imperial shipyard that was kept under tight control. The shipyard produced exclusively Imperial-class Star Destroyers
